
Am - A minor                      C  D  E  F  G   A  B    
1|-|-|-|                          do re mi fa sol la si
2|1|-|-|                                   
3|-|3|-|                         **THE NUMBERS IN THE FRETS ARE THE FINGERS"  
4|-|2|-|                          minor - "smaller" chord, "sad" sound
5|-|-|-|o                         major - "bigger" chord, "happy" sound
6|-|-|-|x
  1 2 3 - the frets              "smaller" and "bigger" refers to the intervals in the chords
---------------------------  
Em - E minor                    o - root note of the chord (always the same name as the chord)
1|-|-|-|                          example:
2|-|-|-|                          root note of "E minor" is "E"
3|-|-|-|                          root note of "A minor" is "A"
4|-|3|-|
5|-|2|-|                          x - do not play string/ mute string 
6|-|-|-|o                             (note that does not reside in the chord)
  1 2 3 

